  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "HR Assistant 5 Days work week/ Central Location",
  "description": "<ul><li><p>Responsible for full spectrum of HR function in areas of recruitment, on-boarding, employee relations, training matters,Payroll, disciplinary matters, etc</p></li><li><p>Manage full cycle recruitment cycle including sourcing, interview, salary proposal, onboarding process/orientation and exit interview</p></li><li><p>Manage employees’ matters in areas of grievances, training program, appraisal for annual increment and performance bonus</p></li><li><p>HR Administrative duties in areas of preparation of all HR related letters, work pass application for renewal and cancellation, insurance, maintaining P-File and HR Documentation, etc</p></li><li><p>Build rapport, engage and sustain good relationship with stakeholders</p></li><li><p>Ensure company regulation and practices are relevant to the Employment Acts and statutory requirements</p></li><li><p>Maintain HR Benefits and Compensation matters, Performance Management, and improvement of internal HR processes</p></li><li><p>Administer and update staff’s database on a timely basis (Times Soft)</p></li><li><p>Update E-cirtrix e-portal and MHC e-portal for staff movement.</p></li><li><p>Verify MHC invoice for Medical check-up and medical claim</p></li><li><p>Checking schedule for staff attendance.</p></li><li><p>Respond to and resolve employee inquiries regarding to payroll issues or concerns</p></li><li><p>Liaise closely with brand managers on schedule, leave application and staff matter</p></li><li><p>Keep track of all employees’ leave records (AL, Sick leave) and update to Timesoft</p></li><li><p>Prepare monthly payroll reports and other related human resource reports</p></li><li><p>Manage all the workmen injury compensation claims and medical claims</p></li><li><p>Prepare staff appraisal form for staff confirmation</p></li><li><p>Prepare and issue Birthday voucher to staffs</p></li><li><p>Ad-hoc duties as assigned by HRM</p></li></ul>",
